cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.DS 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it focuses on improving the performance of binary neural networks on image classification tasks such as CIFAR-10 and ImageNet. It is also likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-categories as it proposes a new regularization function and approximation of the derivative of the activation function to improve the training of binary neural networks. Additionally, it may belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category as binary neural networks are a popular area of research in the field of AI. Finally, it may also belong to the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category as the modifications proposed in the paper are based on linear operations that can be easily implemented into the binary training framework.
